headline: Prologis lifts annual FFO forecast as warehouse leasing rebounds
summary: Warehouse-focused real estate investment trust Prologis on Wednesday raised the bottom of its forecasted range for adjusted core funds from operations in 2025, as customers resumed leasing after U.S. tariffs forced a slowdown in April. Shares of the company rose 2.6% to $111.5 in premarket trading. Although uncertainties around U.S. President Donald Trump's tariffs persist, companies are once again ramping up leasing as they plan inventory for back-to-school and early holiday business.
